text: The District of Columbia participated in the 2020 United States presidential election with the other 50 states on Tuesday, November 3, 2020. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. SenatorKamala Harrishad won 3 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in Washington, D.C.
title: 2020 United States presidential election in the District of Columbia
